    public abstract class AbstractInlineSELECTTestCase
extends AbstractDataAndSPARQLTestCase
    The idea here is that the subclasses provide the data for the test (i.e. the triples, the query and the results) inline and not in separate files. One goal is to reduce the level of redundant comments that can be out of sync. See AbstractDataDrivenSPARQLTestCase for the out-of-line files based approach, which may be more suitable for larger queries, test data or results.

    jeremycarroll
